    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I think a theoretical solution could be to create an optimization phase called `StatementSimplificationRule`, that contains various simplification rules (by pattern matching statements then transform them), including:\r\n\r\n1.\r\n```\r\nfor { } <cond> { <statements-without-function-decl> }\r\n{  <statements-without-break-continue> break }\r\n```\r\n->\r\n```\r\nif <cond> { <statements-without-break-continue> }\r\n```\r\n2.\r\n```\r\nif true { <body> }\r\n```\r\n->\r\n```\r\n{ <body> }\r\n```\r\n3. Bonus: `DeadCodeEliminator` can be expressed as single rule (prerequisite: function hoister):\r\n```\r\n{\r\n<statements-A>\r\n<terminating-statement>\r\n<statements-without-func-decl>\r\n}\r\n```\r\n->\r\n```\r\n{\r\n<statements-A>\r\n<terminating-statement>\r\n}\r\n```",
